        {
            "name": "Rat Swarm",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [],
            "text": "A swarm of rats can cause total chaos within a household or business. Contracting filth fever is all the easier when dozens of these agitated or hungry vermin gather to bite victims en masse, making rat-hunting a viable career in many parts of the world as desperate townspeople seek relief from the disease\u2019s spread.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Animal</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"10\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Nature</a></u>)</b>: DC 15",
            "source": {
                "name": "Bestiary",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                },
                "page": 276
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Rat",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Rats and Disease",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "Rats have a reputation of being\nvicious, aggressive animals\nthat attack food stores in great\nnumbers and spread disease.\nWhile rats are immune to the most\nsevere effects of their own filth\nfever, the disease makes them\nunpredictable and aggressive.\nSome populations of rats carry\neven more deadly diseases, such\nas bubonic plague.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 276
                    },
                    "subtype": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Rats are a ubiquitous menace, scurrying through the sewers and on the streets of nearly every settlement the world over. Though a regular rat darting underfoot might startle or even frighten the average passerby, giant rats and rat swarms are far more dangerous.",
            "source": {
                "name": "Bestiary",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                },
                "page": 276
            }
        }
